# Rust
target/

# Cargo.lock IS committed for this app (see Cargo's recommendation for
# binary/application crates). Without it, every CI run does a fresh
# dependency resolution against crates.io and any newly-published minor
# of e.g. `tauri = "^2"` can break the build with no code change on our
# side — that's how v0.0.17's first release attempt failed (tauri 2.11
# vs @tauri-apps/api 2.10 mismatch). Committing the lockfile pins both
# sides to the same versions across CI and dev.

# Tauri externalBin staging (populated by CI; never committed)
src-tauri/binaries/

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
typescript
*.tsbuildinfo
# Local artisan scripts are excluded by default. Build-essential scripts
# that produce committed artifacts (so future contributors can rebuild
# them) are listed as exceptions below. Note: `!` re-inclusion only
# works against `/scripts/*`, not `/scripts/` — git cannot re-include
# a file once its parent directory is excluded.
/scripts/*
!/scripts/generate-menu-icons.sh
!/scripts/regen-icons.sh
!/scripts/pre-push
!/scripts/install-hooks.sh
# Local CI gate + its shared invariant checks. repo-invariants.sh is
# invoked by .github/workflows/ci.yml, so it MUST be committed.
!/scripts/preflight.sh
!/scripts/repo-invariants.sh
dev-docs/

# Per-clone validator hosts for scripts/pre-push (internal hostnames —
# never committed; real values documented in CLAUDE.local.md).
.validator-hosts

# Claude Code local override files (read alongside CLAUDE.md / AGENTS.md
# but kept out of version control). The general pattern catches any
# *.local.md file anywhere in the tree (the `*.local` pattern above
# only matches files literally ending in `.local`, not `.local.md`).
CLAUDE.local.md
AGENTS.local.md
**/*.local.md

# Tauri's `pnpm tauri icon` command regenerates these on every run,
# but we don't ship for MSIX/iOS/Android, so any reappearance is dead
# bytes. Ignored so a stray `pnpm tauri icon` invocation doesn't
# stage them. The supported regen path is `scripts/regen-icons.sh`,
# which produces only the assets the bundler actually consumes.
src-tauri/icons/Square*Logo.png
src-tauri/icons/StoreLogo.png
src-tauri/icons/128x128@2x.png
src-tauri/icons/ios/
src-tauri/icons/android/

# tdd-guardian generated artifacts
.claude/tdd-guardian/state.json

# loc-guardian local-only thresholds
.claude/loc-guardian.local.md

# Claude harness local task scheduler lock
.claude/scheduled_tasks.lock

# ui-tokenize plugin local state (catalog snapshot + per-pid ledger).
# Regenerated by `/ui-tokenize:init` and the plugin's PreToolUse hook.
.tokenize/

# Environment files — defensive: keep secrets out even if a contributor
# drops a bare `.env` (`*.local` only covers `.env.local`).
.env
.env.*
!.env.example
!.env.sample

# Private keys / credentials — first-line defense for accidental
# `id_rsa` / cert drops. Nothing legitimate at the repo level should
# match these.
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
id_rsa
id_rsa.pub
id_ed25519
id_ed25519.pub
id_ecdsa
id_ecdsa.pub

# Test coverage — `pnpm test:coverage` lands here.
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# Vite / Vitest caches.
.vite/
.vitest-cache/

